---
const features = [
  {
    marker: "01",
    title: "Zero boilerplate",
    body: "Start with a complete, production-ready project structure. Typed errors, structured logging, env config, and CORS middleware are all wired up on day zero.",
  },
  {
    marker: "02",
    title: "Type-safe end-to-end",
    body: "Rust's compile-time guarantees on the backend. TypeScript on the frontend. Two type systems working together so runtime surprises stay rare.",
  },
  {
    marker: "03",
    title: "Your choices, instantly",
    body: "Pick your database, ORM, authentication, and scaffold type in an interactive wizard. You answer; the scaffolder builds the exact project you described.",
  },
  {
    marker: "04",
    title: "Deploy-ready from the start",
    body: "Structured tracing with tracing-subscriber, environment-aware config via dotenvy, and tower-http middleware — the production checklist is already checked.",
  },
];
---

<section class="below-fold py-24 px-6 border-b border-border">
  <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto">

    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="h-px bg-border-2 mb-8"></div>
    <div class="relative flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
      <span class="text-orange text-[0.75rem] leading-none" aria-hidden="true">◆</span>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-[0.8125rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-ink-3">
        WHY RUXUM?
      </h2>
      <span class="absolute right-0 font-mono text-[0.6875rem] text-ink-3/40 select-none">
        04 features
      </span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.6] text-ink-2 max-w-[560px] mb-12">
      Setting up a modern Rust web server is tedious. Picking a framework,
      configuring logging, wiring a database, adding auth — ruxum handles all of
      it so you can focus on your product.
    </p>

    <!-- Feature cards — mosaic grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-border-2 border border-border">
      {features.map((f) => (
        <div class="group relative flex flex-col gap-4 p-8 bg-surface
                    border-t border-border
                    hover:bg-surface-3 hover:border-t-orange/25
                    hover:[box-shadow:inset_0_0_0_1px_rgba(244,67,54,0.12),0_8px_32px_rgba(0,0,0,0.4)]
                    transition-all duration-200">
          <!-- Decorative corner marker -->
          <span class="absolute top-3 right-3 text-[0.5rem] text-border-2 select-none" aria-hidden="true">◇</span>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="w-9 h-9 flex items-center justify-center border border-orange/25 bg-orange/[0.03]
                         font-mono text-[0.625rem] text-orange/80 shrink-0 leading-none">
              {f.marker}
            </span>
            <h3 class="font-mono text-[1rem] font-semibold text-ink tracking-[-0.01em]
                       group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200 pt-2">
              {f.title}
            </h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[0.9375rem] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2 pl-[calc(2.25rem+1rem)]">
            {f.body}
          </p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom CTA row -->
    <div class="mt-8 flex items-center gap-3">
      <a href="/introduction" class="font-mono text-[0.8125rem] text-orange hover:text-orange/80 no-underline transition-colors duration-150">
        read the docs →
      </a>
      <span class="w-px h-3.5 bg-border-2"></span>
      <a href="/scaffold/fullstack" class="font-mono text-[0.8125rem] text-ink-3 hover:text-ink-2 no-underline transition-colors duration-150">
        full-stack guide →
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .grid-cols-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    section { padding-top: 3.5rem; padding-bottom: 3.5rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    section { padding-left: 1rem; padding-right: 1rem; }
  }
</style>
